    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "QANTAS\nRUSTRALIA",
      "CANTAS AIRWAYS\nPOST CARD\nTHE QANTAS 747B is the most advanced 747\nversion yet produced by Boeing. It stands as tall\nas a six-storey building at the tail, and its wings\nstretch nearly 70.51 m from tip to tip. The aircraft\nweighs approx 345 tonnes fully laden ready for take-\noff and has a cruising speed of 920 km/h at 10,668 m.\n2003.105.189\nPrinted in Australia"
    ],
